  },
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:GrammarFoundation",
      "@type": "owl:Ontology",
      "owl:versionInfo": "2.4.0",
      "dcterms:created": "2026-05-12",
      "dcterms:modified": "2026-07-12",
      "dcterms:creator": "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI",
      "dcterms:title": "TSCG M3 Grammar Foundation",
      "dcterms:description": "Apex ontology of the TSCG hierarchy — no imports, no dependencies. Defines the Lambek Calculus mathematical foundation (free commutative monoidal categories), the six indexed operators (×, +, |), abstract classes M3Grammar and MonoidalType, the TSCG type system hierarchy (𝕋₀→𝕄₀), and the intersubjective benchmark properties. Imported by M3_EagleEye, M3_SphinxEye, and M3_GenesisGrammar.",
      "rdfs:label": "M3 Grammar Foundation — TSCG Apex Ontology",
      "rdfs:comment": "Foundational definitions for the TSCG Structural Grammar. Rooted in Lambek Calculus (Lambek 1958) and free commutative monoidal categories (MacLane 1963). The ⊗ operator is a monoidal product — NOT an algebraic tensor product. No metric, no Hilbert space, no scalar multiplication required or assumed.",
      "metadata": {
        "layer": "M3",
        "name": "Grammar Foundation",
        "version": "2.2.0",
        "architecture": "apex — no owl:imports",
        "date_created": "2026-05-12",
        "date_modified": "2026-05-27",
        "authors": [
          "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI"
        ],
        "imported_by": [
          "M3_EagleEye.jsonld",
          "M3_SphinxEye.jsonld",
          "M3_GenesisGrammar.jsonld"
        ],
        "changelog": {
          "v1.1.0": "MAJOR UPDATE: Added dcterms metadata, skos namespace. Fixed owl:versionInfo prefix. Added 6 indexed operators (⊗ᵗ, ⊗ᵐ, Fm2, Fm2, _^ / _$, _^ / _$). Added type system hierarchy (𝕋₀/𝕋₁/𝕋₂/𝕄₀). Added m3:grammar_foundation:intersubjectiveBenchmark and m3:grammar_foundation:defeasibilityStatus. Confirmed apex position: no owl:imports.",
          "v1.0.0": "Initial skeleton: M3Grammar and M3Dimension abstract classes, grammarType and monoidalProduct properties."
        }
      },
      "mathematical_foundation": {
        "formalism": "Lambek Calculus / Free Commutative Monoidal Categories",
        "references": [
          "Lambek, J. (1958). The mathematics of sentence structure. American Mathematical Monthly 65(3): 154-170.",
          "MacLane, S. (1963). Natural associativity and commutativity. Rice University Studies.",
          "MacLane, S. (1971). Categories for the Working Mathematician. Springer."
        ],
        "operator_disclaimer": "⊗ shares notation with the algebraic tensor product but operates in a distinct context: a typed combinatorial grammar without metric structure. Analogous to how × denotes both scalar multiplication and vector cross product — same symbol, different mathematical contexts.",
        "see_also": "ontology/StructuralGrammar/TSCG_StructuralGrammar_as_Mathematical_Foundation_README.md"
      },
      "m2:changelog": [
        {
          "version": "2.4.0",
          "date": "2026-07-12",
          "changes": "SC-1 FUNCTIONAL GRAMMAR MODEL — M3 correction. ⚠ Fm2 and Fm1m2 were declared MORPHISMS ('Fm2 is a morphism, not a monoidal operator'); they are FUNCTIONS. A morphism/functor must preserve composition; emergence is non-compositional (arguments are COMBINED, not associated). Φ and Ψ remain genuine morphisms — the family is now split, not purged. ⚠ Fm1m2 was defined as 'Fm1m2 : 𝕋₁(M1) × 𝕋₁(M2)ⁿ → 𝕋₁, crosses the M1/M2 boundary'. THIS WAS THE ROOT ERROR: it propagated into M1_CoreConcepts v1.4.0, which 'corrected' Propagation/CascadeAmplification Fm2→Fm1m2 'because parent m1:Cascade is M1, not M2 atomic'. Fm1m2 is distinguished by DOMAIN QUALIFICATION, not by crossing a layer boundary; an Fm2 argument may legitimately come from M1_CoreConcepts. Corrected signatures: Fm2 : GenericConcept²⁺ → GenericConceptCombo; Fm1m2 : Domain⁺, GenericConcept⁺ → DomainConceptCombo. The × separating the signature slots is also removed (× is reserved to the Gt monoid and is never overloaded). RENAME: m2:KnowledgeFieldConceptCombo → m2:DomainConceptCombo. See StructuralGrammar/Functional_Grammar_Model.md."
        },
        {
          "version": "2.3.0",
          "date": "2026-07-12",
          "changes": "SC-1 FUNCTIONAL GRAMMAR MODEL. RENAME (hard): m2:DomainConceptCombo → m2:DomainConceptCombo. The class is also RE-DEFINED: a DomainConceptCombo is defined by its Fm1m2 formula — a hybrid of ≥1 Domain and ≥1 GenericConcept (domain qualification), superseding the former 'parents from distinct epistemological domains' criterion. A combo's formula IS the function signature: Fm2 : GenericConcept²⁺ → GenericConceptCombo (≥2 concepts); Fm1m2 : Domain⁺, GenericConcept⁺ → DomainConceptCombo (≥1 domain AND ≥1 concept). No monoidal formula, no monoidal expansion — emergence is non-compositional, so Fm2/Fm1m2 are FUNCTIONS, not functors. Arguments = named concepts from M2_GenericConcepts or M1_CoreConcepts only, comma-juxtaposed, never primitives, never joined by ×/+/|. Fm1 does not exist. ⚠ Formulas in this file are FLAGGED by the new SHACL (v1.1.0) and NOT repaired here — repair belongs to SC-6. See StructuralGrammar/Functional_Grammar_Model.md."
        },
        {
          "version": "2.2.0",
          "date": "2026-05-27",
          "changes": "BASE16 EXTENSION: Gs alphabet extended from 3 to 6 primitives. Three new Gs types: K (Knowledge, idx 3), Ss (Symbol/Stereopsic, idx 4), L (Localizability, idx 5). 𝕋₀ cardinality: 13 → 16. TKSL acronym for the 4 nominal Gs primitives. Transcendental questions map: {T: When?, K: What?, Ss: Sign?, L: Converging?}. 5-5-6 asymmetry documented."
        },
        {
          "version": "2.1.0",
          "date": "2026-05-20",
          "changes": "OPERATOR MIGRATION: monoidalProduct ⊗ⁱ → ×/+/| (three explicit operators). dualityOperator ^opⁱ → _^/_$ (Gs pole primitives). emergenceOperator ⊗ⁱ⇒ removed (replaced by Fm2/Fm1m2). TypeSystem T2 cleaned."
        },
        {
          "version": "2.0.0",
          "date": "2026-05-20",
          "changes": "RENAME: m3:M3Dimension → m3:MonoidalType. MonoidalType class defined."
        }
      ],
      "three_alphabets": {
        "description": "Three primitive alphabets — one per monoidal operator.",
        "territory": {
          "notation": "𝕋₀(×) = {A, S, F, I, D}",
          "grammar": "Territory Grammar Gt — Eagle Eye",
          "operator": "×",
          "neutral": "m3:grammar_foundation:EmptyTerritory",
          "perspective": "What systems ARE"
        },
        "map": {
          "notation": "𝕋₀(+) = {R, E, V, O, Im}",
          "grammar": "Map Grammar Gm — Sphinx Eye",
          "operator": "+",
          "neutral": "m3:grammar_foundation:EmptyMap",
          "perspective": "How models QUALIFY"
        },
        "stereopsis": {
          "notation": "𝕋₀(|) = {T, _^, _$, K, Ss, L}  — symbolic notation only, not URIs",
          "grammar": "Stereopsis Grammar Gs — Bicephalous Perspective",
          "operator": "|",
          "neutral": "m3:grammar_foundation:StereopsisEmptySet",
          "perspective": "How Territory and Map CORRESPOND",
          "cardinality": 6,
          "asymmetry_note": "5-5-6 asymmetry: Gs has 6 primitives because the inter-grammar axis requires encoding convergence discrimination (L) that presupposes both Gt and Gm",
          "acronym": "TKSL — the 4 nominal Gs primitives (T=Temporality, K=Knowledge, Ss=Symbol, L=Localizability). Poles _^/_$ are polarity modifiers, not nominal primitives.",
          "transcendental_questions": {
            "T": "When?",
            "K": "What?",
            "Ss": "Sign?",
            "L": "Converging?"
          },
          "primitives_note": "T=Temporality, _^=PositivePole, _$=NegativePole, K=Knowledge, Ss=Symbol(Stereopsic), L=Localizability. Symbols _^/_$ are string notations only — OWL identifiers: m3:bicephalous:PositivePole, m3:bicephalous:NegativePole",
          "see_also": "M3_BicephalousPerspective.jsonld"
        }
      },
      "operator_grammar_types": {
        "description": "× and + are intra-grammar (closed). | is inter-grammar (open). Explained within Lambek framework only.",
        "intra_grammar": {
          "territory_product": {
            "operator": "×",
            "domain": "Gt × Gt",
            "codomain": "Gt"
          },
          "map_sum": {
            "operator": "+",
            "domain": "Gm × Gm",
            "codomain": "Gm"
          }
        },
        "inter_grammar": {
          "stereopsic_fusion": {
            "operator": "|",
            "domain": "(Gt ∪ Gm ∪ Gs) × (Gt ∪ Gm ∪ Gs)",
            "codomain": "Gs",
            "associativity": "| is associative: (a | b) | c = a | (b | c)",
            "pole_pattern_positive": "expr_Territory | expr_Map | _^  (e.g. Coherence)",
            "pole_pattern_negative": "expr_Territory | expr_Map | _$  (e.g. Incoherence)",
            "precedence": "× > + > |  (highest to lowest)",
            "see_also": "ontology/docs/OntologyModeling_Guidelines.md Guideline 8"
          }
        }
      },
      "m2_functions_and_morphisms": {
        "note": "Φ and Ψ are MORPHISMS (structure-preserving maps between grammars — they compose). Fm2 and Fm1m2 are FUNCTIONS, NOT morphisms and NOT functors: their essence is combination with emergence, which is non-compositional, whereas a morphism/functor must preserve composition. The two families are kept separate on purpose. See StructuralGrammar/Functional_Grammar_Model.md.",
        "description": "Combination FUNCTIONS at M2/M1 level (Fm2, Fm1m2) alongside the genuine inter-grammar MORPHISMS (Φ, Ψ). Distinct from the monoidal operators ×/+/|, which act at 𝕋₀ on atoms. Fm2/Fm1m2 are functions, not morphisms: emergence is non-compositional.",
        "Fm2": {
          "signature": "Fm2 : GenericConcept²⁺ → GenericConceptCombo",
          "description": "GenericConcept composition. Replaces former ⊗⇒ notation.",
          "example_1": "Fm2(Memory, Entropy) = Inertia",
          "example_2": "Fm2(Incoherence, Invariant) = TopologicalDefect",
          "example_3": "Fm2(Process, Step, Trajectory) = PipelineProcess",
          "kind": "function (not a morphism, not a functor) — emergence is non-compositional",
          "arity": "≥ 2 named concepts (M2_GenericConcepts or M1_CoreConcepts). Never primitives. Never joined by ×/+/|."
        },
        "Fm1m2": {
          "signature": "Fm1m2 : Domain⁺, GenericConcept⁺ → DomainConceptCombo",
          "description": "KnowledgeField + GenericConcept composition.",
          "example_1": "Fm1m2(Biology, Process) = BiologicalProcess",
          "example_2": "Fm1m2(Physics, Coherence) = LaserCoherence",
          "kind": "function (not a morphism, not a functor) — emergence is non-compositional",
          "arity": "≥ 1 Domain AND ≥ 1 named concept. Domain QUALIFICATION is what distinguishes Fm1m2 from Fm2 — NOT 'crossing the M1/M2 boundary' (an Fm2 argument may itself come from M1_CoreConcepts)."
        },
        "family": "MORPHISMS: Φ (Gt→Gm), Ψ (Gm→Gt) — structure-preserving, they compose. FUNCTIONS: Fm2, Fm1m2 — emergence, non-compositional, they do NOT compose."
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:M3Grammar",
      "@type": "owl:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "M3 Grammar (Abstract)",
      "rdfs:comment": "Abstract base class for M3-level structural grammars. Concrete subclasses: TerritoryGrammar (Gt, ASFID primitives) and MapGrammar (Gm, REVOI primitives).",
      "skos:definition": "A free commutative monoidal grammar over a finite set of primitive types. Characterized by: primitives (generators), monoidal operator (× for Gt, + for Gm, | for Gs), combination function (Fm2 — emergence, non-compositional), and pole primitives (_^ / _$)."
    },
    {
      "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:MonoidalType_base",
      "@type": "owl:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Monoidal Type Base (formerly M3Dimension)",
      "rdfs:comment": "Abstract base class for M3 primitive types. At M2/M3: generators of structural formulas (qualitative, no metric). At M0: instantiation functors map structural primitives to observable instance values (quantitative scoring belongs to the M0 ValueSpace, not to the M3 structural grammar).",
      "skos:definition": "A primitive type in the TSCG Structural Grammar. Plays two roles: (1) generator of type expressions at M2 level; (2) evaluation functor at M0 level via norm-referenced scoring against intersubjective benchmarks.",
      "skos:note": "The word 'dimension' is used in the analytical sense (independent axis of characterisation), NOT in the metric/Hilbert sense."
    },
    {
      "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:grammarType",
      "@type": "owl:DatatypeProperty",
      "rdfs:label": "Grammar Type",
      "rdfs:comment": "Type of grammar — prevents collision between M3 structural grammar and M0 instance grammar (e.g. SHACL validation grammars).",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:M3Grammar"
      },
      "rdfs:range": {
        "@id": "xsd:string"
      },
      "skos:example": "free_commutative_monoidal"
    },
    {
      "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:monoidalProduct",
      "@type": "owl:DatatypeProperty",
      "rdfs:label": "Monoidal Operators ×, +, |",
      "rdfs:comment": "Three free commutative monoidal operators of TSCG — one per grammar. × (Territory, intra-ASFID), + (Map, intra-REVOI), | (Stereopsis, inter-grammar). Replaces former single indexed form ⊗ⁱ.",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:M3Grammar"
      },
      "rdfs:range": {
        "@id": "xsd:string"
      },
      "skos:definition": "The structural co-activation operator of the TSCG Concept Grammar. Encodes simultaneous presence of multiple primitive types in a concept signature.",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:axioms": {
        "territory_associativity": "(A × B) × C = A × (B × C)",
        "territory_commutativity": "A × B = B × A",
        "territory_neutral": "A × EmptyTerritory = A",
        "map_associativity": "(R + E) + V = R + (E + V)",
        "map_commutativity": "R + E = E + R",
        "map_neutral": "R + EmptyMap = R",
        "stereopsis_associativity": "(a | b) | c = a | (b | c)",
        "stereopsis_neutral": "x | StereopsisEmptySet = x",
        "no_metric": "no norm, no inner product, no scalar multiplication"
      },
      "m3:grammar_foundation:operatorForms": {
        "territory": "×  — Territory structural product (intra-Gt, closed within ASFID)",
        "map": "+  — Map structural sum (intra-Gm, closed within REVOI)",
        "stereopsis": "|  — Stereopsic fusion (inter-grammar, always produces Gs)"
      },
      "m3:grammar_foundation:precedence": "× > + > |  (highest to lowest binding strength)",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:associativity": "All three are associative and commutative",
      "skos:example": "D × It × F = Process  |  R + O = ModelQuality  |  A × S × It | R + O = Coherence"
    },
    {
      "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:dualityOperator",
      "@type": "owl:DatatypeProperty",
      "rdfs:label": "Pole Primitives _^ and _$  (replaces former ^op)",
      "rdfs:comment": "Stereopsis Grammar Gs primitives _^ (PositivePole) and _$ (NegativePole). Applied as: formula | _^  (positive pole)  or  formula | _$  (negative pole). Replaces former duality operator _^ / _$ (vestige of tensor algebra). Defined in M3_BicephalousPerspective.jsonld.",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:M3Grammar"
      },
      "rdfs:range": {
        "@id": "xsd:string"
      },
      "skos:definition": "Dual type operator: maps a concept type to its structural opposite. Corresponds to negation in propositional logic via the Curry-Howard correspondence.",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:pole_forms": {
        "positive": "_^  — PositivePole — applied as: formula | _^",
        "negative": "_$  — NegativePole — applied as: formula | _$",
        "note": "Both _^ and _$ are primitives of 𝕋₀(|) — string notations only, not URIs"
      },
      "skos:example": "A × S × It | R + O | _^  = Coherence  (positive pole)\nA × S × It | R + O | _$  = Incoherence  (negative pole)",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:positivePolePrimitive": "_^  — PositivePole — onset/amplifying pole of a GenericConcept pair",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:negativePolePrimitive": "_$  — NegativePole — terminus/attenuating pole of a GenericConcept pair"
    },
    {
      "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:TypeSystem",
      "@type": "owl:NamedIndividual",
      "rdfs:label": "TSCG Type System",
      "rdfs:comment": "Complete type hierarchy of the TSCG Structural Grammar across all layers.",
      "skos:definition": "Four-level type hierarchy derived from 10 primitive types via 3 operators.",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:levels": {
        "T0": {
          "label": "Primitive Types",
          "notation": "𝕋₀ = 16 primitives (Base16): {A,St,F,It,D} ∪ {R,E,V,O,Im} ∪ {T,_^,_$,K,Ss,L}  (symbolic — _^ _$ are string notations)",
          "cardinality": 16,
          "layer": "M3",
          "role": "generators of the TSCG Structural Grammar",
          "acronyms": {
            "territory": "ASFID — Attractor, Structure, Flow, Information, Dynamics",
            "map": "REVOI — Representability, Evolvability, Verifiability, Observability, Interoperability",
            "stereopsis_nominal": "TKSL — Temporality, Knowledge, Symbol(Ss), Localizability",
            "stereopsis_poles": "_^/_$ — PositivePole / NegativePole (polarity modifiers)"
          },
          "subsets": {
            "territory": "{A, St, F, It, D} — 𝕋₀(×) Gt  (5 primitives — ASFID)",
            "map": "{R, E, V, O, Im} — 𝕋₀(+) Gm  (5 primitives — REVOI)",
            "stereopsis": "𝕋₀(|) Gs — 6 primitives: T (Temporality), _^ (PositivePole), _$ (NegativePole), K (Knowledge), Ss (Symbol/Stereopsic), L (Localizability)  [TKSL + poles]"
          },
          "notation_convention": "In hybrid formulas (containing |), Territory and Map types carry their monoid index: It (Information/Territory), St (Structure/Territory), O (Observability/Map). Pure intra-monoid formulas (A×S×F) and ASFID/REVOI scoring terminology are unaffected."
        },
        "T1": {
          "label": "Derived Types (Named Product Types)",
          "notation": "𝕋₁ = { τ₁ OP τ₂ OP ... OP τₙ  |  τᵢ ∈ 𝕋₀,  OP ∈ {×, +, |} }",
          "layer": "M2",
          "role": "M2 GenericConcepts — named structural formulas",
          "examples": [
            "Process    = D × I × F",
            "Coherence  = A × S × It | R + O",
            "Entropy    = D × F | _$"
          ]
        },
        "T2": {
          "label": "Compound Types (Emergent Combos)",
          "notation": "𝕋₂ = compositions of 𝕋₁ expressions via ×, +, |",
          "layer": "M1",
          "role": "M1 GenericConceptCombos — emergent compound concepts",
          "description": "Higher-order types — complex compositions of 𝕋₁. Emergence operators (Fm2) were defined here but removed (no corpus usage). Composition of GenericConcepts is now expressed via the Fm2 and Fm1m2 FUNCTIONS (not morphisms — emergence is non-compositional)."
        },
        "M0": {
          "label": "Terms (Proof Terms)",
          "notation": "𝕄₀ = { poclets inhabiting a type τ ∈ 𝕋₁ ∪ 𝕋₂ }",
          "layer": "M0",
          "role": "Instances that prove a system inhabits a conceptual type",
          "curry_howard": "Poclet = proof term. δ₁ = degree of proof (Curry-Howard correspondence)."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:intersubjectiveBenchmark",
      "@type": "owl:ObjectProperty",
      "rdfs:label": "Intersubjective Benchmark",
      "rdfs:comment": "Domain-contextualized canonical poclet(s) used as scoring reference for M0 instances. Grounds TSCG measurement in norm-referenced intersubjective consensus. Defeasible by design — valid until superseded by broader consensus.",
      "skos:definition": "A provisional structural attractor of a conceptual domain, identified by multi-cook convergence, domain-contextualized by default, explicitly defeasible, and self-improving through corpus growth.",
      "rdfs:range": {
        "@id": "xsd:string"
      },
      "m3:grammar_foundation:structure": {
        "epistemicScore": {
          "property": "m0:epistemicGap",
          "formula": "||ASFID_mean - REVOI_mean|| / sqrt(2)",
          "range": "[0.0, 1.0]"
        },
        "objectivityLevel": {
          "values": [
            "Subjective",
            "MultiExpertConsensus",
            "CanonCalibrated",
            "ContextualizedBenchmark"
          ],
          "default": "ContextualizedBenchmark"
        },
        "benchmarkRefs": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "uri": "IRI of canonical poclet",
            "domain": "M1 domain  (e.g. m1:Biology, m1:Electronics)",
            "canonType": "DomainSpecific | CrossDomain | Universal",
            "weight": "xsd:float  [0.0, 1.0]"
          }
        },
        "expertConsensus": {
          "numberOfExperts": "xsd:integer",
          "convergenceScore": "xsd:float  (ICC / Cohen kappa)",
          "method": "comparative | absolute | hybrid"
        }
      },
      "m3:grammar_foundation:resolutionOrder": [
        "1. DomainSpecific benchmark  (M1 domain of the poclet)  <- DEFAULT",
        "2. CrossDomain benchmark     (adjacent M1 domain)",
        "3. Universal benchmark       (e.g. M0_AdaptiveImmuneResponse)",
        "4. Free scoring + justification                         <- last resort"
      ],
      "skos:note": "Philosophical grounding: Popper (falsifiability), Kuhn (paradigm shifts), Peirce (limit of inquiry). Mathematical grounding: norm-referenced measurement (Stevens 1946), inter-rater reliability (ICC, Cohen kappa)."
    },
    {
      "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:defeasibilityStatus",
      "@type": "owl:DatatypeProperty",
      "rdfs:label": "Defeasibility Status",
      "rdfs:comment": "Explicit declaration that a benchmark or canonical reference is provisional — valid until superseded by broader consensus. Makes revisability a first-class property of TSCG measurements.",
      "rdfs:range": {
        "@id": "xsd:string"
      },
      "skos:definition": "Defeasible knowledge: held as valid until defeated by stronger evidence or broader consensus. The normal epistemic status of scientific, legal, and practical knowledge.",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:structure": {
        "status": {
          "values": [
            "provisional",
            "established",
            "deprecated"
          ],
          "default": "provisional"
        },
        "validUntil": "superseded_by_better_consensus",
        "revisionTrigger": [
          "new_canonical_poclet_identified",
          "expert_consensus_challenged",
          "domain_expansion",
          "corpus_maturation"
        ]
      },
      "skos:note": "Analogous to stare decisis in law (precedent holds until overruled) and scientific paradigms (Kuhn: valid until anomalies accumulate)."
    },
    {
      "@id": "m3:MonoidalType",
      "@type": "owl:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Monoidal Type",
      "rdfs:comment": "Abstract class for all primitive types of the TSCG free monoidal grammars. Replaces former m3:M3Dimension (vestige of Hilbert-space / tensor formalism). Subclasses: types of Gt (ASFID — ×), types of Gm (REVOI — +), types of Gs (TKSL + poles: T, K, Ss, L, _^, _$ — |). A MonoidalType is a generator of the free monoid 𝕋* on 𝕋₀. Total: 16 primitives (Base16).",
      "skos:definition": "A generator of one of the three TSCG free monoidal grammars (Gt, Gm, Gs). MonoidalTypes are the atomic, irreducible elements from which all structural formula expressions are built via ×, +, and |.",
      "owl:equivalentClass": {
        "rdfs:comment": "Formerly named m3:M3Dimension — renamed to reflect Lambek/monoidal formalism"
      },
      "dcterms:created": "2026-05-20"
    },
    {
      "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:Fm2",
      "@type": "owl:DatatypeProperty",
      "rdfs:label": "Fm2 — GenericConcept Combination (function)",
      "rdfs:comment": "Producing FUNCTION for GenericConceptCombos. Fm2 : GenericConcept²⁺ → GenericConceptCombo. Fm2 is NOT a morphism and NOT a functor: its essence is combination with EMERGENCE, which is non-compositional, while a morphism/functor must preserve composition. (The word 'functor' stays reserved for M0 dimension evaluation F_x : System → Score.) Consequently a combo has NO monoidal expansion: its formula IS this signature. Arguments are ≥2 NAMED CONCEPTS declared in M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld or M1_CoreConcepts.jsonld — never primitive types, never a monoidal expression, juxtaposed by comma and never joined by a grammar operator (×, +, |). Supersedes the retired ⊗⇒ notation.",
      "skos:example": "Fm2(Memory, Entropy) = Inertia  |  Fm2(Incoherence, Invariant) = TopologicalDefect  |  Fm2(Process, Step, Trajectory) = PipelineProcess",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:signature": "Fm2 : GenericConcept²⁺ → GenericConceptCombo",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:operatesAt": "𝕋₁ (GenericConcept level — not 𝕋₀ primitive level)",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "m3:MonoidalType"
      },
      "rdfs:range": {
        "@id": "xsd:string"
      },
      "dcterms:created": "2026-05-20",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:kind": "function",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:functionFamily": "MORPHISMS: Φ (Gt→Gm), Ψ (Gm→Gt) — structure-preserving, they compose. FUNCTIONS: Fm2, Fm1m2 — emergence, non-compositional, they do NOT compose."
    },
    {
      "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:Fm1m2",
      "@type": "owl:DatatypeProperty",
      "rdfs:label": "Fm1m2 — Domain + GenericConcept Combination (function)",
      "rdfs:comment": "Producing FUNCTION for DomainConceptCombos. Fm1m2 : Domain⁺, GenericConcept⁺ → DomainConceptCombo. A HYBRID of at least one Domain and at least one GenericConcept. ⚠ CORRECTION (SC-1, 2026-07-12): Fm1m2 does NOT mean 'the function that crosses the M1/M2 boundary'. That earlier reading was wrong and propagated into the corpus (e.g. Fm1m2(Cascade, Duplication, Network), which has no Domain and is really an Fm2). What distinguishes Fm1m2 from Fm2 is DOMAIN QUALIFICATION — nothing else. An Fm2 argument may legitimately be a named concept from M1_CoreConcepts, so 'crossing M1/M2' distinguishes nothing. Both slots are non-empty; the Domain × Concept hybridisation IS the emergence, so one concept argument suffices. Multi-domain conjunction is carried by juxtaposed domain arguments — Fm1m2(Biology, Chemistry, Catalysis); there is no Fm1 and no reification of composite domains. Fm1m2 is NOT a morphism and NOT a functor (emergence is non-compositional). Supersedes the retired ⊗⇒ notation.",
      "skos:example": "Fm1m2(Biology, Process) = BiologicalProcess  |  Fm1m2(Physics, Coherence) = LaserCoherence  |  Fm1m2(Education, Memory, Structure) = CurriculumDesign",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:signature": "Fm1m2 : Domain⁺, GenericConcept⁺ → DomainConceptCombo",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:operatesAt": "M1/M2 boundary — domain-specific instantiation of generic patterns",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "m3:MonoidalType"
      },
      "rdfs:range": {
        "@id": "xsd:string"
      },
      "dcterms:created": "2026-05-20",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:kind": "function",
      "m3:grammar_foundation:functionFamily": "MORPHISMS: Φ (Gt→Gm), Ψ (Gm→Gt) — structure-preserving, they compose. FUNCTIONS: Fm2, Fm1m2 — emergence, non-compositional, they do NOT compose."
    },
    {
      "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:SpecialElements",
      "@type": "owl:NamedIndividual",
      "rdfs:label": "TSCG Special Elements — Neutral and Limit Elements",
      "rdfs:comment": "Registry of the four special elements of the TSCG monoidal grammar system: neutral elements of ×, +, | and the pseudo-absorbent of |.",
      "dcterms:created": "2026-05-20",
      "EmptyTerritory": {
        "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:EmptyTerritory",
        "rdfs:label": "Empty Territory",
        "rdfs:comment": "Neutral element of ×. Absence of all ASFID types. A × EmptyTerritory = A for all A ∈ 𝕋₀(×).",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:grammar": "Gt",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:operator": "×",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:role": "neutral_element",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:visual": "Black — absence of all ASFID types"
      },
      "EmptyMap": {
        "@id": "m3:grammar_foundation:EmptyMap",
        "rdfs:label": "Empty Map",
        "rdfs:comment": "Neutral element of +. Absence of all REVOI types. R + EmptyMap = R for all R ∈ 𝕋₀(+).",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:grammar": "Gm",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:operator": "+",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:role": "neutral_element",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:visual": "Empty pentagon — absence of all REVOI types"
      },
      "StereopsisEmptySet": {
        "@id": "m3:bicephalous:StereopsisEmptySet",
        "rdfs:label": "Stereopsis Empty Set",
        "rdfs:comment": "Neutral element of |. Defined as EmptyTerritory | EmptyMap. Divergent Strabismus — δ₁ = max. x | StereopsisEmptySet = x for all x.",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:grammar": "Gs",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:operator": "|",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:role": "neutral_element",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:visual": "Black + Empty pentagon",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:epistemicGap": "δ₁ = max",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:definition": "EmptyTerritory | EmptyMap",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:semantics": "Divergent Strabismus — Territory and Map share nothing"
      },
      "StereopsisUniversalSet": {
        "@id": "m3:bicephalous:StereopsisUniversalSet",
        "rdfs:label": "Stereopsis Universal Set",
        "rdfs:comment": "Pseudo-absorbent of |. Defined as 𝕋₀(×) ∪ 𝕋₀(+) ∪ 𝕋₀(|) = 𝕋₀ (16 primitives — Base16). StereopsisUniversalSet | a = StereopsisUniversalSet for all a. Degenerate limit — Borges 1:1 map paradox. Distinct from SpectralClass Coherent (δ₁ ≈ 0).",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:grammar": "Gs",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:operator": "|",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:role": "pseudo_absorbent",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:visual": "White + Full pentagon",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:epistemicGap": "δ₁ = 0",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:definition": "𝕋₀(×) ∪ 𝕋₀(+) ∪ 𝕋₀(|)",
        "m3:grammar_foundation:semantics": "Convergent Strabismus — degenerate limit, not a semantic ideal"
      }
    }
  ]
}